2.00	Alan_Chin_(artist)	Alan Chin (artist)	Alan Christopher Chin (born October 15, 1987) is an American artist working in the San Francisco Bay Area. He has worked in the media of painting, printmaking, drawing, photography, sculpture, and film. He is known for his exploratory paintings and sculptures. Chin studied at California College of the Arts in Oakland, California, and has since shown work in galleries around the world. As a Chinese American artist, Chin draws inspiration from his family heritage, creating works commemorating his familyâ€™s affiliation with the California gold rush and the construction of transcontinental railroad in the western United States the 19th century.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Takashi_Murakami_and_Alan_Chin.jpg/175px-Takashi_Murakami_and_Alan_Chin.jpg
